    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce" percent="100.0">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">Literature. The energy use of the evaporation process is based on the average values of different scientific publications summarized in Pospíšil et al. 2019 (qualified estimates). The material consumption of the evaporation process calculated based on figures given in an environmental study for a LNG terminal in Greece (Asprofos Engineering 2014) (qualified estimates). The infrastructure requirements are based on rough estimates. Reference(s): Pospíšil J., Charvát P., Arsenyeva O., Klimeš L., Špiláček M. and Klemeš J. J. (2019) Energy demand of liquefaction and regasification of natural gas and the potential of LNG for operative thermal energy storage. In: Renewable and Sustainable Energy Reviews, 99, pp. 1-15, 10.1016/j.rser.2018.09.027 Asprofos Engineering 2014 Asprofos Engineering (2014) Cumulative Impacts Assessment for the 2nd Upgrade of the LNG Terminal in Revithoussa Island, Greece.</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">The technology mix in Europe, i.e., 60% open rack vaporizers (ORV) and 40% submerged combustion vaporizers according to Agarwal et al. (2017; in Bussa et al. 2023), is also assumed for other geographies in the database.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
